From Russell Peltz Subject Re How does a pitcher get a save In article mjones fenway writes writes For the record, there are two ways that a reliever can get a save He must finish the game and either have entered the game with the tying run on base, at bat, or on deck have pitched at least three innings effectively A pitcher may not get a win and a save in the same game Close, but there's a number also have entered the game with no more than a run lead and pitched at least one inning If a pitcher finishes a game which his team has won, does not get the win, and satisfies at least one of the three requirements, he gets a save Rusty Russell Peltz P O Box Y S New Haven, CT